    <p>For decades, the Gov­ern­ment’s po­si­tion was that it didn’t make sense to be both pros­e­cut­ing the ac­cused and pay­ing for his de­fence.</p>
    <p>MS STE­FANIE YUEN-THIO, joint man­ag­ing part­ner at TSMP Law Corp. EN­SURE IT IS NOT ABUSED</p>
    <p>The Gov­ern­ment will have to en­sure that peo­ple don’t take ad­van­tage of it, that mem­bers of the pub­lic do not abuse it, and only the needy will be given the le­gal aid.</p>
    <p>CRIM­I­NAL LAWYER RA­JAN SUPRA­MA­NIAM, a con­sul­tant at Ed­mond Pereira Law Corp.</p>


